
[1]exoteric

   EXOT'ERIC, a. [Gr. exterior.] External; public; opposed to esoteric or
   secret. The exoteric doctrines of the ancient philosophers were those
   which were openly professed and taught. The esoteric were secret, or
   taught only to a few chosen disciples.
